# Plain-Language UI (prod)

Audience: novel translators and authors who do **not** know LLM internals, tokenization, or prompt engineering.

**Scope:** production client UI (`src/client/**`). **Out of scope:** Prompt Lab Advanced, `/debug`, engine SSOT in `src/shared/`, docs, logs.

## Two layers of copy

| Layer | Role | Example |
|-------|------|---------|
| **Label** | What the control does | «Глоссарий при переводе» |
| **Hint** | Why change it + trade-off | «Экономит лимит, если глоссарий большой» |

Hints MUST answer: *«Зачем мне это менять?»* — quality, speed, AI daily limit, when to turn off.

## Forbidden in prod labels and hints

Do **not** use in user-facing settings, toggles, option subtitles, or workflow hints:

- chunk / чанк, one-shot, CoT, reasoning, tier, prompt / промпт, JSON, schema
- tok, token counts (except quota/stat screens: `tokenUsage`, `tokenLimit`, `projectInfo.approxTokens`)
- Legacy (use «сохранённая модель» / saved model)
- English jargon in ru/be UI (except model product names: GPT, o4-mini)

Technical marker syntax (`{{block:…}}`) is allowed only in **format integration** help, not in general settings hints.

## Replacement vocabulary

| Avoid | Use (RU orient; localize en/be/pl) |
|-------|--------------------------------------|
| чанк / chunk | часть главы / по частям |
| one-shot | целиком за один проход |
| CoT / reasoning | тщательнее прорабатывает текст (no technique name) |
| N tok / 3000 / 4500 | omit numbers in hints; «короткими порциями» / «крупными частями» if needed |
| меньше токенов | меньше расходует лимит AI |
| в промпте | в инструкции для AI, or omit |
| Режим исполнения | Как обрабатывать текст |

## Standard / Advanced presets

Describe **effect**, not engine mechanics:

- **Standard:** chapter processed in parts — stable default for most chapters.
- **Advanced:** tries whole chapter in one pass — faster on short chapters; long ones still split into parts.

RU labels: «Стандарт» / «Расширенный» (not English «Advanced»).

## Glossary toggles

Focus on name consistency and limit, not chunk sizes:

- **Off (translation):** names aligned at editing; saves AI limit when glossary is large.
- **On:** uses glossary names immediately — more accurate, uses more of today’s AI limit.

## Model descriptions (prod pickers)

Short, outcome-focused `settings.modelDesc.*` for the 3 translate/edit models:

- `gpt-5.4-mini` — best quality, recommended
- `o4-mini` — complex chapters, slower
- `gpt-4.1-mini` — budget option, processes in parts

No one-shot / chunked / reasoning in user-facing model lines.

## Merge checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded UI strings in components
- [ ] Every new hint passes the «зачем мне это?» test
- [ ] No token/chunk numbers in `settings.*` hints
- [ ] ru/be hints free of English jargon (except model names)
- [ ] «Токен» only on quota/stat screens

